# <type>(<scope>): <short description — max 72 chars>
#
# ─── ATOMIC COMMIT CHECKLIST ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ✅ Does this commit do exactly ONE logical thing?
# ✅ Does it build and pass lint on its own?  →  npm run check
# ✅ Can it be reverted without breaking anything else?
# ✅ Is the scope one of:
#    lib | demo | minimal | theme | tokens | a11y | storybook | deps | ci | release | workspace
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# TYPES:
#   feat     → new component or feature
#   fix      → bug fix
#   docs     → documentation only
#   style    → formatting, no logic change
#   refactor → code change, not feat or fix
#   perf     → performance improvement
#   test     → adding or updating tests
#   chore    → build, tooling, deps
#   ci       → CI/CD changes
#   revert   → reverts a previous commit
#
# EXAMPLES:
#   feat(lib): add accessible tooltip component
#   fix(a11y): correct focus trap in dialog
#   chore(deps): update @angular/core to 21.x
#   docs(lib): add CSS custom property API table to button docs
#
# BODY (optional — explain WHY, not what):
#
#
# FOOTER (optional):
#   BREAKING CHANGE: <what breaks and migration path>
#   Closes #<issue-number>
